ble-totalSupply}."},"transferFrom(address,address,uint256)":{"details":"See {IERC721-transferFrom}."}},"stateVariables":{"owner":{"details":"Initially deployer, then account with burn/mint/pause roles (LoanCore)."}},"title":"PromissoryNote","version":1},"userdoc":{"errors":{"ERC721P_DeadlineExpired(uint256)":[{"notice":"Deadline for the permit has expired."}],"ERC721P_InvalidSignature(address)":[{"notice":"Invalid signature."}],"ERC721P_NotTokenOwner(address)":[{"notice":"Address of the owner to also be the owner of the tokenId."}],"PN_AlreadyInitialized()":[{"notice":"Roles have been initialized."}],"PN_BurningRole(address)":[{"notice":"Caller of burn function must have the BURNER_ROLE in AccessControl."}],"PN_CannotInitialize()":[{"notice":"Deployer is allowed to initialize roles. Caller is not deployer."}],"PN_ContractPaused()":[{"notice":"No token transfers while contract is in paused state."}],"PN_MintingRole(address)":[{"notice":"Caller of mint function must have the MINTER_ROLE in AccessControl."}]},"kind":"user","methods":{"DOMAIN_SEPARATOR()":{"notice":"Returns the domain separator used in the encoding of the signature for {permit}, as defined by {EIP712}."},"burn(uint256)":{"notice":"Create a new token and assign it to a specified owner. The token ID         should match a loan ID, and can only be called by a burner - in practice         LoanCore, which burns notes when a loan ends. Also unserts the mapping to         lookup loan IDs by note IDs."},"initialize(address)":{"notice":"Grants owner access to the specified address, which should be an         instance of LoanCore. Once admin role is set, it is immutable,         and cannot be set again."},"mint(address,uint256)":{"notice":"Create a new token and assign it to a specified owner. The token ID         should match the loan ID, and can only be called by the minter. Also         updates the mapping to lookup loan IDs by note IDs."},"nonces(address)":{"notice":"Returns the current nonce for `owner`. Thi